---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About - Neurodivergent Support Coaching" description="Meet your coach and learn about our mission to support Australian families with neurodivergent children through compassionate, experienced guidance.">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <h1>About Our Practice</h1>
          <p class="hero-subtitle">Compassionate support rooted in personal experience and professional expertise</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-image">
          <div class="placeholder-image">
            <!-- Placeholder for professional photo -->
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="story">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="story-content">
        <h2>My Story</h2>
        <p>As a mum of two beautiful neurodivergent children, I understand firsthand the unique joys, challenges, and complexities that come with this journey. My path into coaching wasn't planned – it emerged from my own experiences navigating systems, advocating for my children, and learning to celebrate their incredible differences while supporting their needs.</p>
        
        <p>When my eldest was diagnosed with ADHD and autism at age 7, I felt overwhelmed, isolated, and unsure of how to best support him. The traditional parenting advice didn't apply, school meetings felt intimidating, and I struggled to find my voice as his advocate. Through trial and error, research, and connecting with other families, I slowly built confidence and found strategies that worked for our family.</p>
        
        <p>My younger daughter's learning difficulties and anxiety brought new challenges and insights. Each child's journey has been unique, teaching me that there's no one-size-fits-all approach to supporting neurodivergent children. What works for one family might not work for another, and that's perfectly okay.</p>
        
        <p>After years of supporting other families informally and seeing the positive impact of sharing experiences and strategies, I decided to formalise my passion into professional coaching practice. I wanted to be the support I wished I'd had at the beginning of my journey – someone who truly understood and could guide families with both empathy and practical strategies.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="qualifications">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Qualifications & Training</h2>
      <div class="quals-grid">
        <div class="qual-card">
          <div class="qual-icon">🎓</div>
          <h4>Certified Life Coach</h4>
          <p>International Coach Federation (ICF) Accredited Program</p>
          <p class="institution">Australian Institute of Professional Coaching</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="qual-card">
          <div class="qual-icon">🧠</div>
          <h4>Neurodiversity Specialist</h4>
          <p>Specialised training in ADHD, Autism, and Learning Differences</p>
          <p class="institution">Neurodiversity Training Institute</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="qual-card">
          <div class="qual-icon">👥</div>
          <h4>Family Systems Training</h4>
          <p>Understanding family dynamics and systemic approaches</p>
          <p class="institution">Australian Family Therapy Association</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="qual-card">
          <div class="qual-icon">🏫</div>
          <h4>Educational Advocacy</h4>
          <p>Training in IEP development and educational rights</p>
          <p class="institution">Children with Disability Australia</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="qual-card">
          <div class="qual-icon">🌱</div>
          <h4>Ongoing Education</h4>
          <p>Regular professional development and conference attendance</p>
          <p class="institution">Commitment to staying current with best practices</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="qual-card">
          <div class="qual-icon">❤️</div>
          <h4>Lived Experience</h4>
          <p>Mother of two neurodivergent children</p>
          <p class="institution">15+ years of personal journey and advocacy</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="approach">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>My Approach</h2>
      <div class="approach-content">
        <div class="approach-principles">
          <div class="principle">
            <h4>🌟 Strength-Based Focus</h4>
            <p>I believe every neurodivergent child has unique strengths and gifts. We focus on identifying and nurturing these while addressing challenges with compassion and practical strategies.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle">
            <h4>🤝 Collaborative Partnership</h4>
            <p>You are the expert on your child and family. I bring professional knowledge and personal experience, but you make the decisions. We work together as equal partners.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle">
            <h4>🎯 Practical Solutions</h4>
            <p>Theory is helpful, but what families need are practical, implementable strategies that work in real life. We focus on actionable solutions you can use immediately.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle">
            <h4>🌈 Neurodiversity Affirmation</h4>
            <p>Neurodivergence is not something to be "fixed" – it's a natural variation to be understood, supported, and celebrated. Our goal is thriving, not changing who your child is.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle">
            <h4>🏠 Whole Family Approach</h4>
            <p>Neurodivergence affects the entire family system. We address not just the child's needs, but also sibling relationships, parental wellbeing, and family dynamics.</p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="principle">
            <h4>📈 Progress Over Perfection</h4>
            <p>Small, consistent steps lead to meaningful change. We celebrate progress in all its forms and adjust our approach as your family grows and changes.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="values">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Core Values</h2>
      <div class="values-grid">
        <div class="value-card">
          <h4>Empathy</h4>
          <p>Understanding your experience because I've walked a similar path</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="value-card">
          <h4>Respect</h4>
          <p>Honoring your family's values, culture, and unique circumstances</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="value-card">
          <h4>Inclusivity</h4>
          <p>Welcoming all families regardless of background, structure, or beliefs</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="value-card">
          <h4>Integrity</h4>
          <p>Honest, ethical practice with transparent communication</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="value-card">
          <h4>Growth</h4>
          <p>Commitment to continuous learning and professional development</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="value-card">
          <h4>Hope</h4>
          <p>Believing in your family's potential for growth and happiness</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="personal">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Beyond Coaching</h2>
      <p class="personal-intro">When I'm not working with families, you'll find me:</p>
      
      <div class="personal-grid">
        <div class="personal-item">
          <div class="personal-icon">☕</div>
          <p>Enjoying quiet morning coffee while planning creative activities for my children</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="personal-item">
          <div class="personal-icon">📚</div>
          <p>Reading the latest research on neurodiversity and child development</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="personal-item">
          <div class="personal-icon">🌿</div>
          <p>Gardening – it's my form of meditation and stress relief</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="personal-item">
          <div class="personal-icon">🎨</div>
          <p>Crafting and creating alongside my children (mess and all!)</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="personal-item">
          <div class="personal-icon">🏃‍♀️</div>
          <p>Going for walks or runs to clear my head and stay energised</p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="personal-item">
          <div class="personal-icon">👥</div>
          <p>Connecting with other parents in our local neurodivergent community</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Ready to Connect?</h2>
      <p>I'd love to learn about your family's unique journey and explore how we can work together to create positive change.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Book Your Free Consultation</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

